definitions.definition: The act of stepping down from something being ridden, such as a skateboard .
The part of a routine in which the gymnast detaches from an apparatus.
examples: It was a stylish routine, let down by a sloppy dismount .

main_definition: The act of stepping down from something being ridden, such as a skateboard .
secondary_definitions: ( gymnastics ) The part of a routine in which the gymnast detaches from an apparatus.
